en (thawed) berries instead.","Fruit purées like this one also make a lovely addition to your baby's porridge or rice cereal if you're serving one. Just be sure to give your baby plenty of savoury purées too. Fruit is nutritious and it's important that your baby develops a liking for various fruit flavours but offering less sweet options is crucial too.","Kefir, a fermented milk drink, is similar to a thin yoghurt with a mild fizz. Its nutritional profile varies considerably depending on production methods but milk kefir is typically a more potent probiotic with a broader range of beneficial bacteria than yoghurt. Kefir has also been found to be more digestible than yoghurt in individuals with lactose intolerance. Make it yourself or choose an unflavoured, unsweetened brand with active probiotic cultures."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","30m","1"]}